--- !u!114 &3565468141906147812
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 9073611175433636603}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fbeb6d65be27d3b40a131a1e4ace56b5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  steps:
  - message: What's up, {player}!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Gizmo, I can\u2019t finish the hovercraft calibration. Look, it keeps
      shaking side to side when I power it on. What\u2019s wrong?"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Nice question! You probably mixed up scalars and vectors again.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 2
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Scalars and vectors? Remind me what those are.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 2
    endTime: 3
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Okay look closely, {player}! Scalars only tell us how much, not which
      way. See this? The number line shows 5 kg of weight and 10 seconds of time,
      both have no direction.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 3
    endTime: 4
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Ahhh whether it\u2019s positive or negative, a scalar\u2019s value
      just shows the amount \u2014 like measuring how heavy or how long, never where
      it\u2019s going."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Now let\u2019s move on to vectors! Unlike scalars, vectors have magnitude
      and direction \u2014 they tell us how much and where."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "See this arrow? Its length shows the magnitude (7.21), and its angle
      points to the direction \u2014 in this case, 34\xB0 East-North-East."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 5
    endTime: 6
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Velocity, acceleration, and force are all vectors because they describe
      both \u201Chow much\u201D and \u201Cwhich way.\u201D"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 6
    endTime: 7
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Then my engine thrust must be off in direction, not strength.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 7
    endTime: 8
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Correct! That\u2019s why understanding vector direction is key to keeping
      your hovercraft balanced."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Let\u2019s go deeper \u2014 vectors can be shown using projections."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 8
    endTime: 9
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Projection means showing how much of a vector lies along another direction
      \u2014 kind of like casting a shadow on an axis."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 9
    endTime: 10
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: 1D projection represents a vector along a single straight line or axis,
      showing direction in only one dimension.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 10
    endTime: 11
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: '2D projection, represents a vector on a plane using two components:
      the x-axis and y-axis to show both magnitude and direction.'
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 11
    endTime: 12
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "So the vector has components \u2014 one horizontal (x) and one vertical
      (y)."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 12
    endTime: 13
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: 'Exactly! And 3D projection, represents a vector in space using three
      components: x, y, and z to describe its direction and magnitude in all three
      dimensions.'
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 12
    endTime: 13
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: But how do I know if the components are positive or negative?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 13
    endTime: 14
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Great question! It depends on the quadrant where the vector lies.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Quadrant I is +x, +y; Quadrant II is -x, +y; Quadrant III is -x, -y;
      and Quadrant IV is +x, -y.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 14
    endTime: 15
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "So, if my thrust points up-left, that\u2019s Quadrant II \u2014 x-component
      is negative and y-component is positive."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 15
    endTime: 16
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Correct! Changing the sign changes the direction of your vector.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Speaking of direction, what happens if I completely reverse my vector?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Then you get a negative vector \u2014 same magnitude, but rotated 180\xB0,
      pointing the opposite way."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 16
    endTime: 17
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Ohh, so that\u2019s why my hovercraft moves backward when I reverse
      thrust!"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 17
    endTime: 18
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Exactly! Now, let\u2019s talk about unit vectors \u2014 these show
      only direction because their magnitude is one."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 18
    endTime: 19
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "So if I divide a vector by its magnitude, I get a unit vector that
      tells me just where it\u2019s pointing?"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Perfectly said! That\u2019s written as F-hat = F / |F|, meaning \u201Cforce
      in direction only.\u201D"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So mastering vectors helps me control both the power and direction of
      my hovercraft.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Exactly, {player}! Once you understand scalars and vectors, you\u2019re
      not just flying \u2014 you\u2019re navigating physics itself."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 19
    endTime: 20
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
